{"mode":"editor","version":1,"windowDimensions":{"x":254,"y":23,"width":1024,"height":752,"maximized":false},"grammars":{"deserializer":"GrammarRegistry","grammarOverridesByPath":{}},"project":{"paths":["/Users/joegesualdo/Desktop/greenmile"],"buffers":[{"text":"﻿1\r\n00:00:21,815 --> 00:00:23,732\r\nHey! What are you doing?\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:00:28,154 --> 00:00:30,197\r\n- Jesus.\r\n- Did you get a good look?\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:00:30,198 --> 00:00:32,240\r\nBlue Toyota camry.\r\nThat's all I saw.\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:00:32,241 --> 00:00:33,492\r\nThat's the Whartons' dog.\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:00:33,493 --> 00:00:35,243\r\nAw, man.\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:00:35,244 --> 00:00:37,955\r\nHe's not going to make it.\r\nGo see if they're home.\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:49,800\r\nShh. Shh.\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:00:49,801 --> 00:00:52,135\r\nIt's okay.\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:56,849\r\nThere are two kinds of pain...\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:00:56,850 --> 00:00:59,059\r\nThe sort of pain that makes you strong,\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:00:59,060 --> 00:01:01,020\r\nor useless pain,\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:01:01,021 --> 00:01:04,147\r\nthe sort of pain that's only suffering.\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:01:04,148 --> 00:01:07,401\r\nI have no patience for useless things.\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:12,072\r\nMoments like this require\r\nsomeone who will act,\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:01:12,073 --> 00:01:15,242\r\nwho will do the unpleasant thing,\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:01:15,243 --> 00:01:17,745\r\nthe necessary thing.\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:23,751\r\nThere.\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:01:23,752 --> 00:01:25,544\r\nNo more pain.\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:30,382\r\nIt was a hit-and-run.\r\nI'm awfully sorry.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:01:30,383 --> 00:01:32,509\r\nHe must have jumped\r\nover the fence again.\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:01:32,510 --> 00:01:34,511\r\nLook, Steve is going to file\r\nthe report on the car,\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:01:34,512 --> 00:01:36,179\r\nand he'll put his people on it.\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:01:36,180 --> 00:01:38,097\r\nWe'll track them down.\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:01:57,868 --> 00:02:00,829\r\nYou look stunning. Shall we?\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:02:00,830 --> 00:02:03,331\r\nThree, two, one...\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:02:03,332 --> 00:02:05,834\r\nHappy new year!\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:02:12,049 --> 00:02:14,593\r\nOh. President-elect\r\nGarrett Walker.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:02:14,594 --> 00:02:16,136\r\nDo I like him? No.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:02:16,137 --> 00:02:17,972\r\nDo I believe in him?\r\nThat's beside the point.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:02:17,973 --> 00:02:20,181\r\nAny politician\r\nthat gets 70 million votes\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:02:20,182 --> 00:02:22,392\r\nhas tapped into something\r\nlarger than himself...\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:02:22,393 --> 00:02:24,645\r\nLarger than even me,\r\nas much as I hate to admit it.\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:02:24,646 --> 00:02:27,606\r\nAnd look at that winning smile,\r\nthose trusting eyes.\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:02:27,607 --> 00:02:30,609\r\nI latched onto him early on\r\nand made myself vital.\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:02:30,610 --> 00:02:32,527\r\nAfter 22 years in congress,\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:02:32,528 --> 00:02:34,989\r\nI can smell which way\r\nthe wind is blowing.\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:02:34,990 --> 00:02:36,490\r\nOh, Jim Matthews,\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:02:36,491 --> 00:02:38,200\r\nhis right honorable\r\nvice-president.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:02:38,201 --> 00:02:39,952\r\nFormer governor of Pennsylvania.\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:02:39,953 --> 00:02:42,329\r\nHe did his duty in delivering\r\nthe keystone state,\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:02:42,330 --> 00:02:43,831\r\nbless his heart,\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:02:43,832 --> 00:02:45,666\r\nand now they're about\r\nto put him out to pasture.\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:47,709\r\nBut he looks happy enough, doesn't he?\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:02:47,710 --> 00:02:51,839\r\nFor some, it's simply\r\nthe size of the chair.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,590\r\nHuh.\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:02:53,591 --> 00:02:55,926\r\nLinda vasquez, Walker's chief of staff.\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:02:55,927 --> 00:02:57,344\r\nI got her hired.\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:02:57,345 --> 00:02:59,596\r\nShe's a woman, check,\r\nand a latina, check,\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:02:59,597 --> 00:03:01,140\r\nbut more important than that,\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:03:01,141 --> 00:03:03,182\r\nshe's as tough\r\nas a two-dollar steak.\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,726\r\nCheck, check, check.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:03:04,727 --> 00:03:06,269\r\nWhen it comes to the white house,\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:03:06,270 --> 00:03:08,522\r\nyou not only need the keys\r\nin your back pocket,\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:03:08,523 --> 00:03:10,065\r\nyou need the gatekeeper.\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:03:10,066 --> 00:03:12,734\r\nAs for me, I'm just\r\na lowly house majority whip.\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:03:12,735 --> 00:03:14,569\r\nI keep things moving in a congress\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:03:14,570 --> 00:03:16,780\r\nchoked by pettiness and lassitude.\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:03:16,781 --> 00:03:19,950\r\nMy job is to clear the pipes\r\nand keep the sludge moving.\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:03:19,951 --> 00:03:21,910\r\nBut I won't have to be\r\na plumber much longer.\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:03:21,911 --> 00:03:24,371\r\nI've done my time.\r\nI backed the right man.\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:03:25,414 --> 00:03:27,332\r\nHappy new year!\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,126\r\nGive and take.\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:03:29,127 --> 00:03:31,210\r\nWelcome to Washington.\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:11,478\r\nYou need a haircut.\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:05:11,479 --> 00:05:12,896\r\nYou think?\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:05:12,897 --> 00:05:14,856\r\nA little trim.\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:05:16,108 --> 00:05:17,776\r\nWhat are you going to wear?\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:05:17,777 --> 00:05:20,028\r\n- You mean for the meeting?\r\n- For the announcement.\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:05:20,029 --> 00:05:22,990\r\nGonna wear my Navy blue,\r\nthe one with the pinstripes.\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:05:22,991 --> 00:05:26,160\r\nGood. You look handsome\r\nin that suit.\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:05:27,410 --> 00:05:28,996\r\nI don't know if they'll announce it\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:05:28,997 --> 00:05:30,538\r\nbefore your board meeting.\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:05:30,539 --> 00:05:32,207\r\nWell, as long as I can say\r\nthe donation is coming.\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:05:32,208 --> 00:05:33,750\r\nAs soon as it's official,\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:05:33,751 --> 00:05:36,086\r\nSancorp will write you a check.\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:05:38,922 --> 00:05:42,092\r\nThis is going to be a big year for us.\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:05:56,148 --> 00:05:58,275\r\nYou know, the meeting's on Tuesday.\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:02,279\r\nYou're gonna wanna\r\nstart with something...\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:03,864\r\nThat's what I'm hearing.\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:06:03,865 --> 00:06:05,406\r\nCommunity of what?\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:06:05,407 --> 00:06:07,701\r\nOr I could say immigration,\r\nbanking, or education,\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:06:07,702 --> 00:06:10,037\r\nbut none of my regular sources\r\ncan confirm that.\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:06:10,038 --> 00:06:11,830\r\nBecause they don't know,\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:06:11,831 --> 00:06:13,540\r\nor because they're not talking?\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:06:13,541 --> 00:06:15,000\r\nBecause they don't know.\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:06:15,001 --> 00:06:17,252\r\nKeep at it. Get me something.\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:06:17,253 --> 00:06:20,255\r\nSorry.\r\nSorry, Mr. Hammerschmidt.\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:06:20,256 --> 00:06:22,549\r\nZoe.\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:24,885\r\n- Barnes.\r\n- Right.\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:06:27,846 --> 00:06:30,182\r\nDid it take him a year\r\nto remember your name?\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:06:30,183 --> 00:06:31,183\r\nLonger.\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:06:31,184 --> 00:06:33,392\r\nGood morning, Lucas.\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:34,811\r\nWhat can I do for you, Zoe?\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:06:37,438 --> 00:06:39,649\r\nI am sick of the Fairfax county council.\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:06:39,650 --> 00:06:41,235\r\nYou tell me every day.\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:06:41,236 --> 00:06:43,028\r\nMove me online. My own blog...\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:06:43,029 --> 00:06:45,530\r\nFirst person, subjective, 500 words.\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:06:45,531 --> 00:06:47,741\r\n- Not going to happen.\r\n- I'll go underground.\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:06:47,742 --> 00:06:49,243\r\nBack rooms. The urinals.\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:06:49,244 --> 00:06:51,078\r\nI'll win over staff members on the hill.\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:06:51,079 --> 00:06:53,163\r\n- They need a place to vent.\r\n- A gossip column.\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:06:53,164 --> 00:06:55,707\r\nNo. We lift the veil,\r\nwhat's really going on.\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:57,584\r\nThis is the Washington herald, Zoe.\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:06:57,585 --> 00:06:59,378\r\nIt's not TMZ.\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:06:59,379 --> 00:07:00,712\r\nDo you know how many people watch TMZ?\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:07:00,713 --> 00:07:02,089\r\nI couldn't care less.\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:07:02,090 --> 00:07:03,882\r\nWhich is why print journalism is dying.\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:07:03,883 --> 00:07:06,051\r\nThen it'll die with dignity,\r\nat least at this paper.\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:07:06,052 --> 00:07:09,096\r\nYou are stuck in the 20th century, Lucas.\r\nYou lack imagination.\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:07:09,097 --> 00:07:10,389\r\nMaybe so, but right now,\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:07:10,390 --> 00:07:12,349\r\nI don't need imagination.\r\nI need copy.\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:07:12,350 --> 00:07:14,226\r\nYour nights and weekends are yours.\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:07:14,227 --> 00:07:15,769\r\nI applaud whatever you want to do,\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:07:15,770 --> 00:07:17,478\r\nas long as it's not on my time.\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:07:17,479 --> 00:07:19,647\r\n- You're telling me to get back to work.\r\n- I am.\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:07:19,648 --> 00:07:22,525\r\nWhat you're really telling me\r\nis to fuck off.\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:07:22,526 --> 00:07:24,152\r\nI'm telling you both.\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:31,743\r\nIt's Mr. Chapman already\r\nfrom province trust.\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:38,917\r\nHold my calls, Christina.\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:44,131\r\nHenry. It's good to see you.\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:07:44,132 --> 00:07:46,216\r\n- How long are you in town for?\r\n- Just today.\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:07:46,217 --> 00:07:48,427\r\nWell, you gotta come back down\r\nfor the inauguration.\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:07:48,428 --> 00:07:50,470\r\nI can hook you up.\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:07:50,471 --> 00:07:52,680\r\nHow about you hook me up with the zoning\r\nlaws you promised to get changed?\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:07:52,681 --> 00:07:54,682\r\nWe got 12 million sitting in escrow\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:07:54,683 --> 00:07:56,559\r\nfor an empty lot we can't build on.\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,270\r\nI know, but you gotta understand,\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:07:58,271 --> 00:07:59,520\r\nit's a local municipal issue.\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:01,522\r\nI can't just pick up the phone...\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:08:01,523 --> 00:08:04,025\r\nYou can't? Because that's not\r\nwhat you led us to believe\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:08:04,026 --> 00:08:06,153\r\nwhen you begged\r\nfor 50 grand in donations.\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:08:06,154 --> 00:08:08,947\r\nRight. I...\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:08:08,948 --> 00:08:10,157\r\nOne second.\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:08:10,158 --> 00:08:11,574\r\nChristina, I said no calls,\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:08:11,575 --> 00:08:13,785\r\nnot while I'm meeting\r\nwith Mr. Chapman.\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:08:15,536 --> 00:08:17,831\r\nThe president-elect?\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:08:19,166 --> 00:08:20,792\r\nI... do you mind?\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:08:20,793 --> 00:08:22,043\r\nNo. Go ahead, please.\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:08:22,044 --> 00:08:23,878\r\nUh, put him through, Christina.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:08:23,879 --> 00:08:25,380\r\nAhem.\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:08:27,799 --> 00:08:29,717\r\nMr. president-elect?\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:34,931\r\nThank you.\r\nUh, yes, we were, uh...\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:08:34,932 --> 00:08:37,558\r\nWe were pleased to win by double digits.\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:40,354\r\nAbsolutely. Anything you need.\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:08:40,355 --> 00:08:43,648\r\nI need you to put your\r\nlong, wet, talented tongue\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:08:43,649 --> 00:08:45,233\r\nbetween my thighs\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:08:45,234 --> 00:08:47,861\r\nand make me squeal like Monica Lewin...\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:51,865\r\nMe, too. Me, too.\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:54,742\r\nOkay. Thank you, sir.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:58,872\r\nI'm so sorry.\r\nUh, where were we?\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:09:00,165 --> 00:09:02,417\r\nWalker...\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:09:02,418 --> 00:09:04,044\r\nWhat's he like?\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:09:17,182 --> 00:09:19,184\r\nMr. president-elect\r\nrunning late?\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:09:19,185 --> 00:09:21,936\r\nNo, he couldn't make it.\r\nI'll brief him, though.\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:09:23,146 --> 00:09:25,606\r\nOkay. This is the memo\r\nI've drafted\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:09:25,607 --> 00:09:27,734\r\non our middle east policy\r\nwe've been developing.\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:09:27,735 --> 00:09:29,652\r\nNow, I want to borrow from Reagan.\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:09:29,653 --> 00:09:32,364\r\nI'd like to coin the phrase\r\n\"trickle-down diplomacy.\"\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:09:32,365 --> 00:09:35,409\r\n- That way...\r\n- Frank, I'm going to stop you there.\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:38,286\r\nWe are not nominating you\r\nfor secretary of state.\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:09:38,287 --> 00:09:40,163\r\nI know he made you a promise,\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:09:40,164 --> 00:09:41,915\r\nbut circumstances have changed.\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:43,542\r\nThe nature of promises, Linda,\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:09:43,543 --> 00:09:46,836\r\nis that they remain immune\r\nto changing circumstances.\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:09:46,837 --> 00:09:49,172\r\nGarrett has thought long\r\nand hard about this,\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:09:49,173 --> 00:09:52,050\r\nand he's decided we need you\r\nto stay in congress.\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:09:52,051 --> 00:09:54,761\r\nWhen was this decision made,\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:09:54,762 --> 00:09:57,138\r\nand why wasn't I part\r\nof the conversation?\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:09:57,139 --> 00:09:58,723\r\nI'm sorry, Frank.\r\nIf it had been up to me,\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:09:58,724 --> 00:10:00,308\r\nI wouldn't have waited\r\nthis long to tell you.\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:10:00,309 --> 00:10:02,602\r\nSo, you knew you were going to do this.\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:10:02,603 --> 00:10:04,479\r\nIt has been an evolving discussion.\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:07,566\r\nIt's a chicken-shit move.\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:08,942\r\n- Frank...\r\n- I was vetted.\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:10:08,943 --> 00:10:10,360\r\n- Was that a ruse?\r\n- No.\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:10:10,361 --> 00:10:11,652\r\nLet's be absolutely clear.\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:13,654\r\nYou wouldn't have won without me.\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:10:13,655 --> 00:10:15,407\r\nYou're right, but now we have to lead,\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:10:15,408 --> 00:10:17,951\r\nand that means making tough choices.\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:10:17,952 --> 00:10:20,828\r\nAs you know, education\r\nis a top priority for us,\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:10:20,829 --> 00:10:22,539\r\na complete federal overhaul.\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:24,958\r\nBut it's not just education.\r\nFrank, congress is split.\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:10:24,959 --> 00:10:29,337\r\nWe need you there more than we\r\nneed you in the state department.\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:10:29,338 --> 00:10:31,548\r\nI got you hired, Linda.\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:34,175\r\nI know.\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:10:34,176 --> 00:10:35,552\r\nDonations, endorsements.\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:10:35,553 --> 00:10:37,137\r\nI wrote the campaign's\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:10:37,138 --> 00:10:39,139\r\nentire foreign policy platform.\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:10:39,140 --> 00:10:41,600\r\nI bring years of\r\nforeign affairs committee...\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:10:41,601 --> 00:10:43,935\r\nFrank, please.\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,815\r\nI want to speak to Walker personally.\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:10:48,816 --> 00:10:51,025\r\nThe decision is made.\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:57,449\r\nWe need you, Frank.\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:10:57,450 --> 00:10:59,826\r\nWill you stand beside us or